(Careful, that command destroys all data on the Stick)!!!

https://github.com/joyent/mi-centos-7

Kickstart in a USB:




1. ISO file: rhel-server-7.0-x86_64-dvd.iso

2. mount -o loop rhel-server-7.0-x86_64-dvd.iso /mnt/

3. mkdir /rhel7/

4. rsync -avz /mnt/ /rhel7/

5. put your kickstart file into /rhel7
   cp /path/ks.cfg /rhel7

6. add new lines to /rhel7/isolinux/isolinux.cfg 

label linux_ks
  menu label ^Red Hat Enterprise Linux with Kickstart
  kernel vmlinuz
  append initrd=initrd.img  ks=hd:sdb1:/ks.cfg  
(append initrd=initrd.img  inst.ks=cdrom:/dev/cdrom:/ks.cfg)

7. create the ISO with:
/usr/bin/genisoimage  -o /whenever/rhel-server-7.0-KS-x86_64-dvd.iso /rhel7/

8. dd if=/whenever/rhel-server-7.0-KS-x86_64-dvd.iso of=/dev/XXX (where XXX is the Device Name of your USB drive without the partition number e.g.


(Careful, that command destroys all data on the Stick)!!!


